Package models

Class MemberDatabase

java.lang.Object
models.MemberDatabase
public class MemberDatabase
extends java.lang.Object
The MemberDatabase class contains a list of all the members of the gym, stored in an array of Member objects. This class also includes methods to print the members based on different sorted fields.
Author:
Jackson Lee, Serena Zeng

      Finds index of a member in the member database

      private void grow()
      Grow the member list mlist by GROWTH_FACTOR

    • add

      member - to be added
      Returns:
      false if member already exists in database

    • remove

      public boolean remove​(Member member)
      Remove a member from the gym database
      Parameters:
      member - Member to be removed
      Returns:
      false if member does not exist, otherwise true

    • printDefault

      public void printDefault()
      If there are no members, a message indicating database is empty is printed. Otherwise, a list of members is printed without sorting.

    • printWithFees

      public void printWithFees()
      If there are no members, a message indicating database is empty is printed. Otherwise, a list of members and their fees is printed without sorting.

    • print

      private void print​(boolean includeFees)
      Print the members in the database (without headers)
      Parameters:
      includeFees - whether or not to include the fees

    • printByLocation

      public void printByLocation()
      If there are no members, a message indicating database is empty is printed. Otherwise, print the list of members sorted in place by county, then zip code.

    • printByExpirationDate

      public void printByExpirationDate()
      If there are no members, a message indicating database is empty is printed. Otherwise, print the list of members sorted in place by expiration date of membership.

    • printByName

      public void printByName()
      If there are no members, a message indicating database is empty is printed. Otherwise, print the list of members sorted in place by last name, then first name.

    • contains

      public boolean contains​(Member member)
      Check whether the member database contains the given member
      Parameters:
      member - Member object being checked for
      Returns:
      true if member in database, otherwise false

    • getMember

      public Member getMember​(Member member)
      Gets the Member object from the member database that is equivalent to the given Member object (typically does not contain all fields)
      Parameters:
      member - Target Member object
      Returns:
      Member object from member database with no null fields

    • loadMembers

      public void loadMembers()
      Reads members line by line from the text file memberList.txt and loads the members into the member database.
